# Keep the Docker build context small — and the build hermetic.
#
# App's image builds with ./App as its context (see .github/workflows/docker.yml),
# so the repo-root .dockerignore does NOT apply here: Docker only reads the
# .dockerignore at the root of the build context. Home is unaffected because it
# builds from the repo root and is covered by that file.
#
# `dist` is the important one. The build stage does `COPY . .` and then
# `npm run build`, but tsc does not prune stale outputs — so without this, a
# local dist/ is copied in and any orphaned .js from a since-deleted source
# survives alongside the fresh output. TypeORM globs dist/server/db/migrations
# at boot, so an orphaned migration there is loaded and can kill the container
# on startup. Everything in dist/ is regenerated inside the image anyway.
.git
node_modules
dist
data

# Local tooling and editor state — never needed to build.
.claude
coverage
**/.vite
**/.cache
